<div class="head1"> <a name="gm">Helen Mumford</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Senior Vice President and General Manager, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA) </i>
<p />
Helen Mumford joined Gartner in 1995, following the acquisition of Wentworth Research, where she was chief operating officer. Before taking up her present role, Helen led the global Executive Programs business, working with Gartner chief information officer (CIO) clients, observing, understanding and explaining IT issues and trends.
<p />

Helen is noted for her views on the CIO role and the function of IT, presenting both to CIOs and at Board level, on these and a range of related topics, such as innovation, leadership and communication.
<p />

Before Wentworth Research, Helen was CIO of a general electric capital business in Europe and previously worked as a managing consultant within Ernst & Young's financial services practice, where she focused on large systems implementation and business transformation projects.
<p />

Helen started her career at Andersen Consulting and then spent several years in major financial organisations. <p />
She has a degree in Geography from Oxford University.
<p />
