<div class="head1"><a name="research">Peter Sondergaard</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Group Vice President, Research, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA)
</i>
<p />

Peter Sondergaard joined Gartner in November 1988 as a program director for the personal computing research area, specialising in the overall desktop issues of European users. He advanced to the position of European director of research, where he was responsible for research integrity, integration and methodology. Peter is currently group vice president for Research in EMEA, responsible for its management and direction throughout the region.
<p />

Prior to joining Gartner, Peter was a research director at International Data Corporation in Europe, where his priorities were PC analysis and consulting projects for large European vendors and users. Peter also worked for Scandinavian Airlines System (SAS), where he was responsible PC integration between hotels and SAS data.
<p />

Peter has a master's degree in economics from the University of Copenhagen. He has also contributed to and written for various European trade and business publications.    

