<div class="head1"><a name="comm_exp">Nick Kirkland</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Group Vice President, Executive Programs, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA)</i>
<p />


Nick Kirkland joined Gartner in 2001 and has more than 20 years' experience in information technology and services. Previously, he was director of information services and a Board member at Penguin Books, where his work on creating a unified knowledge-sharing infrastructure was adopted by Microsoft as case study video-training material. Nick was also Sony's U.K. head of IT and he has experience in publishing, FMCG retail and financial services sectors.
<p />

Nick has a business-orientated perspective on technology use with expertise in people management and leadership issues relating to change implementation. During his time as an IT director, he implemented SAP, delivered Web-enabled "self service" applications to customers and worked on enhancing the supply chain through timely information management.
<p />

Nick has also worked extensively in the field of customer relationship management (CRM). His key approach in this area is to design a culture change programme alongside software implementation, for maximum benefit to both the client and organisation. 
<p />

Nick speaks regularly at conferences on all aspects of IT leadership. He is a non-executive director Board member of Tunbridge Wells Equitable Friendly Society and is a member of the Institute of Directors and the Institute for the Management of Information Systems.    
<p />

Nick has a degree in mineral sciences from the University of Leeds.
<p />
