<div class="head1"><a name="measurement">John Grech</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Group Vice President, Measurement, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA)</i>
<p />

John Grech joined Gartner in September 1995 to establish a new IT Measurement and benchmarking business. Initially, he was responsible for setting up the related Measurement application services in EMEA. In 1998, John became manager of Measurement in EMEA and also managed the expansion of the region's Consulting services group. 
<p />

As Group Vice President for Measurement, John is responsible for the management and direction of all EMEA Measurement businesses, managing the full range of services, including decision tools, assessments and performance management services. Gartner Measurement operates in all main EMEA sites and has ISO9002 accreditation for its processes in consistent delivery of high value and high quality services.
<p />

Prior to joining Gartner, John spent more than 15 years' in IT and business consulting, providing both strategic and technical advice in financial, commercial and manufacturing organisations and central government. He has held senior management roles in both end-user and service provider organisations.
<p />
