<div class="head1"><a name="news">Simon Levin</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Group Vice President, News and Client Services, Europe, Middle 

East and Africa (EMEA)</i>
<p />


Simon Levin joined Gartner in August 1994. His management responsibilities incorporate Client 

Services, Editing and Media Services, Business Development (Gartner Connects, Multi-Media, 

Webcast and Alliances) and gartner.com.
<p />

Prior to Gartner, Simon was an international database-marketing manager at Software 

Publishing, a PC-based application software vendor. He was responsible for the development of 

marketing strategy and tactics for all markets outside the United States. 
<p />

He was also an executive information system (EIS) product manager at Information Builders, 

where he was responsible for identifying and implementing an EIS product line within the 

Focus family of products.
<p />


Simon holds a Bachelor's degree from York University.
