<div class="head1"><a name="con1">Malcolm Swallow</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>
Group Vice President, Consulting, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA)</i>
<p />

Malcolm Swallow joined Gartner in April 1997 and has more than 23 years' experience in the 

information technology industry, from working in a variety of environments and technology 

platforms.
<p />

Highlights of previous Consulting engagements include:-
<p />

<ul>

<li>The development and implementation of a networking architecture for a global services 

company</li>

<li>A viability review and assessment of the life and pension systems of a large financial 

services organisation</li>

<li>Leading an outsourcing project for a large pharmaceutical company</li>

<li>Creating an integrated IT strategy for a university as part of a business process 

re-engineering exercise</li>

<li>Reviewing the implementation of a global accounting application for one of the world's 

largest shipping organisations.</li>


<li>Creating a strategy for a core retail banking system, which included risk assessment and a review of the development methodology.</li></ul><p />


Prior to Gartner, Malcolm was a business consulting practice leader for a large database and applications software company. Here, he was involved with technology selection, acquisition 

and implementation, developing IT strategies and producing system and client/server 

architecture designs. 
<p />


Malcolm has extensive systems management, development and implementation experience and is an 

accredited quality auditor. He has also been responsible for outsourcing reviews, the 

selection of partners and supplier management.
<p />
