 <td valign="top">
<div class="head1"><a name="consult">Metaxia-Maria Karagianni</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Chief of staff, Consulting, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA)</i>
<p />


Meta Karagianni joined Gartner in January 1999 as a member of the U.K. Consulting team, focusing on market and business strategy. Her main areas of expertise lie in customer relationship management (CRM), e-business applications and solutions, the assessment of new business models (for example, application service providers (ASP) and e-marketplaces). She also has experience in strategic advice and guidance, especially for vendors targeting the financial services industry.
<p />

Meta transferred to her current position as chief of staff in April 2002. Working alongside EMEA senior management, her role focuses on supporting the region's operations, strategy and internal projects.
<p />


Prior to joining Gartner, Meta worked as a consultant for the Institute of Language and Speech Processing (ILSP) in Greece and she spent three years working in the Greek travel market, gaining significant experience in the service sector.
<p />


Meta has a Bachelor degree in Information Science from the University of Business and Economics in Athens and an MBA from Strathclyde University in Glasgow. She is multi-lingual, speaking fluent Greek, English, French and Spanish.
<p />
