 <td valign="top">
<div class="head1"><a name="events">Jon Graves</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Vice President, International Events, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA) </i>


<p />
Jon Graves is responsible for the Gartner Conference business in EMEA and Asia Pacific. The portfolio of events includes Symposia in Cannes, Florence, Sydney and South Africa along with many subject specific conferences across Europe and Australia. 
<p />
Jon believes that the quality and impartiality of the Gartner Analysts, ensures that IT professionals benefit from the very best conference experience at a Gartner event and take away real business advice. Also, attending a Gartner conference or Symposium is the most effective way for non-Gartner clients to sample the enormous value of becoming a client.
<p /> 
Before joining Gartner in 2000, Jon held various roles in publishing, exhibition and conference companies, with a particular focus on IT Events. in the mid 90s Jon launched the successful "SoftWorld" brand of Application Software events across North America and as the US CEO steered the company from start up to market leader. During his 16 year career in events, nine of which were spent in the US, Jon has also held roles in sales, business development and project management. Jon has worked in markets as diverse as Contemporary Art, IT and wine.
<p />
Jon holds a Bachelor's degree in Art History, from South Wales.   
