 <td valign="top">
<div class="head1"><a name="general">Nick Smith</a></div>
<span class="contentText"><i>Vice President, General, Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA) </i>


<p />
Nick Smith is a vice president and chief client officer in Gartner EMEA. He is focused on understanding and enhancing the Gartner client experience. Based in the U.K., his role involves working with clients and Gartner LOBs across EMEA, acting as an advocate for the client.
<p />
Mr. Smith has over 20 years of experience working in and consulting to technology businesses. His previous positions in Gartner were EMEA chief of staff and leader of market and business strategy consulting for e-business. Immediately prior to joining Gartner, Mr. Smith managed marketing and strategic planning for Kalamazoo International, a United Kingdom-based software and services business with revenue of around $100 million.
<p />
Mr. Smith studied at the University of Edinburgh, graduating with a Master of Arts degree (with honors), first class, in English and American literature and language.
